 elements of the any same type that can grow and shrink in size. We keep track of a few member variables size: number of elements in the vector capacity: space allocated for elements // initialization of vector std::vector vec1{3, 5}; // {3, 5} std::vector vec2(3, 5); // {5, 5, 5} // add element vec1.push_back(4); // {3, 5, 4} // get element int a = vec1.at(0); // a = 3 int b = vec1[1]; // b = 5 DequeA deque is a double ended queue, can do everything a vector can do, unlike vector, it is possible and fast to push_front and pop_front. std::deque dq; // add element dq.push_front(2); // {2} dq.push_front(4); // {4, 2} dq.push_back(3); // {4, 2, 3} // delete element dq.pop_front() // {2, 3} dq.pop_back() // {2} 引用 Which to use? vector is the type of sequence that should be used by default, deque is the data structure of choice when most insertions and deletions take place at the beginning or at the end of the sequence. —— C++ ISO Standard ``` Choosing sequence containers MapMaps are implemented with key-value pairs with unique keys, std::pair Based on ordering property of keys, keys need to be comparable using \u003c operator. Ordered maps/sets require a comparison operator to be deﬁned, keys in sorted order. Unordered maps/sets require a hash function to be deﬁned, keys are unordered. 示例 std::map mymap; string str = mymap.at(key); // throw error if the key not exists. str = mymap[key]; // will not throw error if the key not exists. MultimapMultimap is an associative container that contains a sorted list of key-value pairs, while permitting multiple entries with the same key. 示例 std::multimap myMMap; myMMap.insert({std::make_pair(3, 3)}); myMMap.insert({3, 12}); cout \u003c\u003c myMMap.count(3) \u003c\u003c endl; // 2 SetSets contains a sorted set of unique objects of type Key. 示例 std::set myset; // add element myset.insert(\"game\"); // {\"game\"} myset.insert(\"milk\"); // {\"game\", \"milk\"} // check if contains element bool game_exist = myset.count(\"game\"); // true bool hello_exist = myset.count(\"hello\"); // false // remove element myset.earse(\"milk\"); // {\"game\"} ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec05_containers/:2:1","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec05 Containers","uri":"/2023/01/lec05_containers/#set"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" Container AdaptorsContainer adaptors are “wrappers” to existing containers Wrappers modify the interface to sequence containers and change what the client is allowed to do/how they can interact with the container. Commonly used data structures made easy for the client to use. Can use different backing containers based on use type. Container adaptors wrap existing containers to permit new/restrict access to the interface for the clients. StackStack just limits the functionality of a vector/deque to only allow push_back and pop_back. QueueQueue just limits the functionality of a deque to only allow push_back and pop_front. ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec05_containers/:2:2","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec05 Containers","uri":"/2023/01/lec05_containers/#container-adaptors"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" Container AdaptorsContainer adaptors are “wrappers” to existing containers Wrappers modify the interface to sequence containers and change what the client is allowed to do/how they can interact with the container. Commonly used data structures made easy for the client to use. Can use different backing containers based on use type. Container adaptors wrap existing containers to permit new/restrict access to the interface for the clients. StackStack just limits the functionality of a vector/deque to only allow push_back and pop_back. QueueQueue just limits the functionality of a deque to only allow push_back and pop_front. ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec05_containers/:2:2","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec05 Containers","uri":"/2023/01/lec05_containers/#stack"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" Container AdaptorsContainer adaptors are “wrappers” to existing containers Wrappers modify the interface to sequence containers and change what the client is allowed to do/how they can interact with the container. Commonly used data structures made easy for the client to use. Can use different backing containers based on use type. Container adaptors wrap existing containers to permit new/restrict access to the interface for the clients. StackStack just limits the functionality of a vector/deque to only allow push_back and pop_back. QueueQueue just limits the functionality of a deque to only allow push_back and pop_front. ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec05_containers/:2:2","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec05 Containers","uri":"/2023/01/lec05_containers/#queue"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":"CS106L 课程笔记","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec06_iterators_and_pointers/","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec06 Iterators and Pointers","uri":"/2023/01/lec06_iterators_and_pointers/"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" Iterators","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec06_iterators_and_pointers/:1:0","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec06 Iterators and Pointers","uri":"/2023/01/lec06_iterators_and_pointers/#iterators"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" What is iteratorIterator is a abstraction for a tool that accesses the next or previous element or random access. How do we access elements in a container in order? Containers all implement something called an iterator to do this. Iterators let you access all data in containers programmatically. Iterators allow iteration over any container, whether it is ordered or not. An iterator has a certain order, it “knows” what element will come next. Each container has its own iterator, which can have different behavior. All iterators implement a few shared operations: Initializing -\u003e iter = s.begin(); begin() and end() return iterators. Incrementing -\u003e iter++; Dereferencing -\u003e a = \\*iter; Comparing -\u003e iter != s.end(); Copying -\u003e new_iter = iter; Similarities Can be created from existing iterator. Can be advanced using ++ Can be compared with == and != 示例 std::set\u003cint\u003e myset{1, 2, 3, 4}; // define a iterator like this: // container_class_name::iterator iterator_name; std::set\u003cint\u003e::iterator iter = myset.begin(); cout \u003c\u003c *iter \u003c\u003c endl; // 1 ++iter; cout \u003c\u003c *iter \u003c\u003c endl; // 2 if (iter == myset.end()){ return; } // find returns an iterator std::vector\u003cint\u003e vec{3, 1, 4, 8, 5, 9, 2, 6, 7, 0}; const int elem2find = 5; auto find_it = std::find(vec.begin(), vec.end(), elem2find); cout \u003c\u003c *find_it \u003c\u003c endl; // 5 // map iterator std::map\u003cint, int\u003e mmap; for(auto iter = mmap.begin(); iter != mmap.end(); ++iter){ cout \u003c\u003c (*iter).first \u003c\u003c \" \" \u003c\u003c (*iter).second \u003c\u003c endl; // is the same as ... cout \u003c\u003c iter-\u003efirst \u003c\u003c \" \" \u003c\u003c iter-\u003esecond \u003c\u003c endl; } ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec06_iterators_and_pointers/:1:1","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec06 Iterators and Pointers","uri":"/2023/01/lec06_iterators_and_pointers/#what-is-iterator"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" Types of iterator Input and output iterators: They can perform sequential single-pass input or output operations. Forward iterators: They have all the functionality of input iterators and if they are not constant iterators also have the functionality of output iterators. Bidrectional iterators: They are like forward iterators but can also be iterated through backwards. Random-access iterators: They implement all the functionality of bidirectional iterators, and also have the ability to access ranges non-sequentially. Forward iterators are the minimum level of functionality for standard containers. Input iterators can appear on the RHS (right hand side) of an = operator, like auto elem = *it; Output iterators can appear on the LHS (left hand side) of an = operator, like *elem = value; Bidirectional iterators can go forward as well as backward. ++it; --it; Random-access iterators allow you to directly access values without visiting all elements sequentially. it += 5; Collected by xyx: 示例 for (auto iter = set.begin(); iter != set.end(); ++iter){ do something; } // dereference the iterator to get element const auto\u0026 elem = *iter; ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec06_iterators_and_pointers/:1:2","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec06 Iterators and Pointers","uri":"/2023/01/lec06_iterators_and_pointers/#types-of-iterator"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" RangesWe can iterate through different ranges. ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec06_iterators_and_pointers/:1:3","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec06 Iterators and Pointers","uri":"/2023/01/lec06_iterators_and_pointers/#ranges"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" Range based for loopA range based for loop is a shorthand for iterator code. All that is required is that the class contains the member functions begin() and end() and that its **return value type supports the operators ++, * and != ** 示例 // for(type variable : container) std::map\u003cstring, int\u003e mmap; for(auto thing : mmap){ dosomething(thing.first, thing.second) } // the implementation for (it = mmap.begin(); it != mmap.end(); ++it){ thing = *it; dosomething(thing.first, thing.second) } // for structure container (cpp17 extension) for(auto [key, value] : mmap){ dosomething(key, value); } ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec06_iterators_and_pointers/:1:4","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec06 Iterators and Pointers","uri":"/2023/01/lec06_iterators_and_pointers/#range-based-for-loop"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" Pointers","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec06_iterators_and_pointers/:2:0","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec06 Iterators and Pointers","uri":"/2023/01/lec06_iterators_and_pointers/#pointers"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" What is pointerVariables created in code take up space on the computer. They live in memory at speciﬁc addresses. Pointers reference those memory addresses and not the object themselves. Pointer can access memory addresses with \u0026 and the data at an address/pointer using *. 示例 int val = 18; int* ptr = \u0026val; // dereference cout \u003c\u003c *ptr \u003c\u003c endl; // 18 // dereference of member variables struct Student{ int id; string name; }; Student s1{12, \"Alice\"}; Student* ptr = \u0026s1; cout \u003c\u003c ptr-\u003eid \u003c\u003c endl; // 12 std::pair\u003cint, string\u003e game{2, \"Death Loop\"}; std::pair\u003cint, string\u003e* pgame = \u0026game; cout \u003c\u003c pgame-\u003efirst \u003c\u003c endl; // 2 cout \u003c\u003c pgame-\u003esecond \u003c\u003c endl; // Death Loop ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec06_iterators_and_pointers/:2:1","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec06 Iterators and Pointers","uri":"/2023/01/lec06_iterators_and_pointers/#what-is-pointer"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":"CS106L 课程笔记","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec07_classes/","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec07 Classes","uri":"/2023/01/lec07_classes/"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" ClassesClass: A programmerdeﬁned custom type. An abstraction of an object or data type. An Object is an instance of a Class. When a class is deﬁned, no memory is allocated but when it is instantiated (i.e. an object is created) memory is allocated. Classes provide their users with a public interface and separate this from a private implementation. 示例 class Student { public: std::string getName(); void setName(std::string name); int getAge(); void setAge(int age); private: std::string name; std::string state; int age; }; Public section: Users of the specific object can directly access anything here. Deﬁnes interface for interacting with the private member variables. Private section: Usually contains all member variables. Users can’t access or modify anything in the private section. ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec07_classes/:1:0","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec07 Classes","uri":"/2023/01/lec07_classes/#classes"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" Namespaces Put code into logical groups, to avoid name clashes. Each class has its own namespace. Syntax for calling/using something in a namespace: namespace_name::name Function deﬁnitions with namespaces. Inside the {…} the private member variables for namespace_name will be in scope. std::string Student::getName() {...}, we can use private member variables in this function. ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec07_classes/:1:1","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec07 Classes","uri":"/2023/01/lec07_classes/#namespaces"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" This keywordthis is the pointer which points out the object that calls the member function. this-\u003eelement_name means “the item in this specific object with name element_name. Use this for avoiding naming conﬂicts. 示例 void Student::setName(std::string name){ this-\u003ename = name; } ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec07_classes/:1:2","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec07 Classes","uri":"/2023/01/lec07_classes/#this-keyword"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" Constructors The constructor is called every time a new instance is created Deﬁne how the member variables of an object is initialized. Use initializer lists for speedier construction. 示例 // construction using initializer lists // no parameters Student::Student() : name{\"\"}, age{0}, state{\"\"} {} // with parameters Student::Student(string name, int age, string state) : name{name}, age{age}, state{state} {} ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec07_classes/:1:3","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec07 Classes","uri":"/2023/01/lec07_classes/#constructors"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" Array Arrays are a primitive type. They are the building blocks of all containers Think of array as lists of objects of ﬁxed size that you can index into. 示例 int *intarray; // initialize an array int* *intarray = new int[10]; // index into an array int elem = intarray[0]; ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec07_classes/:1:4","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec07 Classes","uri":"/2023/01/lec07_classes/#array"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" Destructors Deleteing (almost) always happens in the destructor of a class. The destructor is deﬁned using class_name::~class_name() the destructor is called when the object goes out of scope. ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec07_classes/:1:5","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec07 Classes","uri":"/2023/01/lec07_classes/#destructors"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" Static memberStatic member meas this member is belong to the class instead of the specific object. static variable must have definition. 示例 class Game { public: Game(/* args */); ~Game(/* args */); void setID(int id) { Game::id = id; } int getID() { return id; } private: /* data */ static int id; }; In this code, id is a variable member belong to the class Game, if we call obj.setID(val), the variable Game:：id wouble be changed. 示例 int main(void) { Game game1; game1.setID(2); cout \u003c\u003c \"game1 id: \"; cout \u003c\u003c game1.getID() \u003c\u003c endl; // 2 Game game2; cout \u003c\u003c \"game2 id: \"; cout \u003c\u003c game2.getID() \u003c\u003c endl; // 2 return 0; } ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec07_classes/:1:6","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec07 Classes","uri":"/2023/01/lec07_classes/#static-member"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":"CS106L 课程笔记","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec08_templates/","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec08 Templates","uri":"/2023/01/lec08_templates/"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" Template","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec08_templates/:1:0","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec08 Templates","uri":"/2023/01/lec08_templates/#template"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" Function TemplateFunction Template: A function template defines a family of functions. The simple idea is to pass data type as a parameter so that we don’t need to write the same code for different data types. 示例 // we need `typename` or `class` keyword template \u003ctypename T\u003e // default parameter types template \u003ctypename T=int\u003e T myMax(T x, T y) { return (x \u003e y) ? x : y; } // function call int int_max = myMax\u003cint\u003e(2, 7); // int_max = 7 double double_max = MyMax\u003cdouble\u003e(2.4, 5.1); // double_max = 5.1 // template arguments deduction myMax(1, 2); // infers that T is of type `int` myMax(1.2, 3.9); // infers that T is of type `double` myMax('a', 'i'); // infers that T is of type `char` Explicit instantiation specify the type T cout \u003c\u003c myMax\u003cint\u003e(2, 3) \u003c\u003c endl; Implicit instantiation leave the type for the compiler to deduce cout \u003c\u003c myMax(2, 3) \u003c\u003c endl 技巧 template functions are not compiled until used! For each instantiation with different parameters, the compiler generates a new specific version of your template at compile time. Template code is instantiated at compile time. ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec08_templates/:1:1","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec08 Templates","uri":"/2023/01/lec08_templates/#function-template"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" Class TemplateClass Template: A class that is parametrized over some number of types. A class that is comprised of member variables of a general type/types. Use generic typenames as placeholders. 示例 template\u003ctypename F, typename S\u003e // we can specify a default value for template arguments // etc. template\u003ctypename F, typename S=int\u003e class MyPair { public: First getFirst(); Second getSecond(); void setFirst(First f); void setSecond(Second f); private: First first; Second second; }; // must announce every member function is templated template\u003ctypename F, typename S\u003e First MyPair::getFirst(){ return first; } // nested dependent type template\u003ctypename F, typename S\u003e typename MyPair\u003cF, S\u003e::iterator MyPair\u003cF, S\u003e::begin() {...} // here iterator is a `dependent type` in namespace Mypair\u003cF, S\u003e:: // we must add `typename` prior Templated code implementation should never be in a .cpp file: your compiler has to see them at the same time as it sees the code that calls them. ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec08_templates/:1:2","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec08 Templates","uri":"/2023/01/lec08_templates/#class-template"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" Generic ProgrammingGeneric Programming is a programming paradigm for developing efficient, reusable software libraries. Generics is the idea to allow type (Integer, String, … etc) to be a parameter to methods, classes and interfaces. Generics can be implemented in C++ using Templates. The advantages of Generic Programming are Code Reusability Avoid Function Overloading Once written it can be used for multiple times and cases. ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec08_templates/:1:3","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec08 Templates","uri":"/2023/01/lec08_templates/#generic-programming"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" Template MetaprogrammingNormally, code runs during runtime. But with template metaprogramming(TMP), code runs once during compile time. Something runs once during compiling and can be used as many times as you like during runtime. 示例 template \u003cunsigned n\u003e struct Factorial { enum {value = n * Factorial\u003cn-1\u003e::value}; }; template\u003c\u003e // template class `specialization` struct Factorial\u003c0\u003e { enum {value = 1}; }; cout \u003c\u003c Factorial\u003c10\u003e::value \u003c\u003c endl; // print 3628800 struct is similar to class in that it can contain both member variables and member functions. the difference of struct and class When using class, the members of a class are all private by default, while when using struct, the members of a struct are all public by default. class can be used as a template keyword, while struct cannot. class inheritance is private inheritance by default, while struct inheritance is public inheritance by default ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec08_templates/:1:4","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec08 Templates","uri":"/2023/01/lec08_templates/#template-metaprogramming"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":"CS106L 课程笔记","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec09_funcs_and_lambdas/","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec09 Functions and Lambdas","uri":"/2023/01/lec09_funcs_and_lambdas/"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" Predicate FunctionsAny function that returns a boolean value is a predicate. A predicate can have any amount of parameters. 示例 bool isVowel(char c){ std::string vowel = \"aeiou\"; return vowel.find(c) != std::string::npos; } // to use predicate template \u003ctypename InputIt, typename UniPred\u003e int count_occurrences(InputIt begin, InputIt end, UniPred pred){ int count = 0; for (auto iter = begin; iter != end; ++iter){ if(pred(*iter)) count++; } return count; } std::string str = \"xadia\"; count_occurrences(str.begin(), str.end(), isVowel); Here UniPred is called a function pointer. Function pointers can be treated just like other pointers. They can be passed around like variables as parameters or in template functions. They can be called like functions. ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec09_funcs_and_lambdas/:1:0","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec09 Functions and Lambdas","uri":"/2023/01/lec09_funcs_and_lambdas/#predicate-functions"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" LambdasLambdas are inline, anonymous functions that can know about variables declared in their same scope. 示例 // complete format of lambda expression [ capture list ] ( params ) mutable(optional) constexpr(optional)(c++17) exception attribute -\u003e return_type { function body } int limit = 5; auto isMoreThan = [limit] (int n) {return n \u003e limit;}; isMoreThan(6); // true // specify the return type `int` auto add = [](int a, int b) -\u003e int { return a + b; }; // assignment is forbidden auto funa = [] { cout \u003c\u003c \"A\" \u003c\u003c endl; }; auto funb = [] { cout \u003c\u003c \"B\" \u003c\u003c endl; }; funa = funb; // error auto func = funa; // ok, copy is permitted Lambdas can capture any outside variable by using [], both by reference and by value. Use a lambda when you need a short function or to access local variables in your function. If you need more logic or overloading, use function pointers. Whenever a lambda expression is defined, the compiler will automatically generate an anonymous class, we call it closure class, this class overloads () operator of course. 示例 class Closure { public: // ... ReturnType operator(params) const { body }; }; ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec09_funcs_and_lambdas/:2:0","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec09 Functions and Lambdas","uri":"/2023/01/lec09_funcs_and_lambdas/#lambdas"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" FunctorsA functor is any class that provides an implementation of operator(). They can create closures of “customized” functions. 警告 Actually, this name never appears in the standard c++, we usually call it function object. Closure: a single instantiation of a functor object. The STL standard function object: std::function\u003creturn_type(param_types)\u003e func; ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec09_funcs_and_lambdas/:3:0","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec09 Functions and Lambdas","uri":"/2023/01/lec09_funcs_and_lambdas/#functors"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":"CS106L 课程笔记","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec10_operator_overloading/","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec10 Operator Overloading","uri":"/2023/01/lec10_operator_overloading/"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" Operators Just like declaring functions in a class, we can declare operator functionality. When we use the operator with our new object, it performs a custom function or operation. Just like in function overloading, if we give it the same name, it will override the operator’s behavior. ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec10_operator_overloading/:1:0","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec10 Operator Overloading","uri":"/2023/01/lec10_operator_overloading/#operators"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" Operators can’t be overloaded Scope Resolution: :: Ternary: ? Member Access: . Pointer-to-member access: .* Object size, type, and casting: sizeof()、typeid()、cast() ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec10_operator_overloading/:1:1","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec10 Operator Overloading","uri":"/2023/01/lec10_operator_overloading/#operators-cant-be-overloaded"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" The way of overloading operators Member functions With member function overloading, we have access to this-\u003e and its private variables. Non-member functions (this way is preferred by the STL) It allows the LHS to be a non-class type. It allows us to overload operators with classes we don’t own. The friend keyword allows non-member functions or classes to access private information in another class. 示例 // first way class Student{ public: /* ... */ // member function // this function would pass `this` as parameter friend bool operator \u003c (const Student\u0026 rhs){ age \u003c rhs.age; }; private: /* ... */ int age; }; // second way class Student{ public: /* ... */ // non-member function friend bool operator \u003c (const Student\u0026 lhs, const Student\u0026 rhs); private: /* ... */ int age; }; // non-member function(global) bool operator \u003c (const Student\u0026 lhs, const Student\u0026 rhs) { return lhs.age \u003c rhs.age; }; Non-member function(global function) of operator overloading(global overloading) 示例 struct Time { int hours; int minutes; int seconds; }; std::ostream\u0026 operator\u003c\u003c(std::ostream\u0026 out, const Time\u0026 time) { out \u003c\u003c time.hours \u003c\u003c \":\" \u003c\u003c time.minutes \u003c\u003c \":\" \u003c\u003c time.seconds; return out; } Time t1{12, 20, 56}; cout \u003c\u003c t1; // 12:20:56 The implementation of \u003c\u003c operator in STL basic_ostream. 示例 template\u003ctypename _Traits\u003e inline basic_ostream\u003cchar, _Traits\u003e\u0026 operator\u003c\u003c(basic_ostream\u003cchar, _Traits\u003e\u0026 __out, const char* __s) { if (!__s) _out.setstate(ios_base::badbit); else _ostream_insert(__out, __s, static_cast\u003cstreamsize\u003e(_Traits::length(__s))); return __out; } 警告 Be careful with non-member overloading. Certain operators, like new and delete, don’t require a specific type. ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec10_operator_overloading/:1:2","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec10 Operator Overloading","uri":"/2023/01/lec10_operator_overloading/#the-way-of-overloading-operators"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" Rules and Philosophy Meaning should be obvious when you see it. Functionality should be reasonably similar to corresponding arithmetic operations When the meaning isn’t obvious, give it a normal name instead. ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec10_operator_overloading/:1:3","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec10 Operator Overloading","uri":"/2023/01/lec10_operator_overloading/#rules-and-philosophy"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":"CS106L 课程笔记","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec11_special_member_functions/","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec11 Special Member Functions","uri":"/2023/01/lec11_special_member_functions/"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" Special member functionsThere are six special member functions, These functions are generated only when they’re called: Default constructor: Takes no parameters and creates a new object. Destructor: Called when an object goes out of scope. Copy constructor: Creates a new object as a member-wise copy of another. Copy assignment operator: Assigns an already existing object to another. Move constructor Move assignment operator We don’t have to write out any of these. They all have default versions that are generated automatically. ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec11_special_member_functions/:1:0","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec11 Special Member Functions","uri":"/2023/01/lec11_special_member_functions/#special-member-functions"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" Copy and copy assignmentBy default, the copy constructor will create copies of each member variable. This is member-wise copying. Many times, we will want to create a copy that does more than just copies the member variables. Deep copy: An object that is a complete, independent copy of the original. // copy constructor Type::Type(const Type\u0026 other) // copy assignment Type::operator=(const Type\u0026 other) ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec11_special_member_functions/:1:1","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec11 Special Member Functions","uri":"/2023/01/lec11_special_member_functions/#copy-and-copy-assignment"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" Default and deletedefault and delete are key words in c++. Declaring any user-deﬁned constructor will make the default disappear. If we need to use the default special member function we need add =default. =default is only used for special member functions of the class that have no default parameters. Can be defined either inside the class body (inline) or outside the class body (out-of-line). 示例 class Student { public: // member function Student(int age); Student() = default; // defulated default constructor. ~Student(); private: int age; }; Student::Student(int age) : age(age) {} Student::~Student() {} Student s0; // error if there is no defaulted function Student s1(19); Student s2(29); Setting a special member function to =delete removes its functionality. Thus we can selectively allow functionality of special member functions. =delete can not be used at destructor. 示例 class Student { public: // member function Student(int age); Student() = default; // defulated default constructor. ~Student(); Student(const Student\u0026 rhs) = delete; // delete the copy constructor Student\u0026 operator=(Student\u0026 other) = delete; // delete the copy assignment // ~Student() = delete; // error, destructor can't be deleted private: int age; }; Student::Student(int age) : age(age) {} Student::~Student() {} Student s1(19); Student s2(s1); // error, copy constructor has been deleted Student s3; s3 = s2; // error, copy assignment has been deleted ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec11_special_member_functions/:1:2","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec11 Special Member Functions","uri":"/2023/01/lec11_special_member_functions/#default-and-delete"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" Move and move assignmentMove constructors and move assignment operators will perform “memberwise moves”. Deﬁning a move assignment operator prevents generation of a move copy constructor, and vice versa. Move constructors and operators are only generated if: No copy operations are declared. No move operations are declared. No destructor is declared. If we want to explicitly support move operations, we can set the operators to default: When the item on the right of the = is an r-value we should use move assignment. r-values are always about to die, so we can steal their resources. r-value referenceDifferent with l-value reference, we use \u0026\u0026 to present r-value reference. move assignment 示例 vector\u003cT\u003e\u0026 operator=(vector\u003cT\u003e\u0026\u0026 other) { if (\u0026other == this) return *this; _size = other._size; _capacity = other._capacity; //we can steal the array delete[] _elems; _elems = other._elems; return *this; } std::movestd::move function mainly converts a l-value into a r-value reference. Use std::move to force the use of other types’ move assignments and constructors. 示例 vector\u003cT\u003e\u0026 operator=(vector\u003cT\u003e\u0026\u0026 other) { if (\u0026other == this) return *this; _size = std::move(other._size); _capacity = std::move(other._capacity); //we can steal the array delete[] _elems; _elems = std::move(other._elems); return *this; } vector\u003cstring\u003e vec1 = {\"hello\", \"world\"}; // vec1 = {\"hello\", \"world\"} vector\u003cstring\u003e vec2 = std::move(vec1); // vec2 = {\"hello\", \"world\"} // vec1 = {} vec1.push_back(\"game\"); // vec1 = {\"game\"} // `vec1` is a l-value, we use `std::move` to convert it // also break the variable `vec1` After a variable is moved via std::move, it should never be used until it is reassigned to a new variable. 警告 Don’t use std::move outside of class definitions, never use it in application code. ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec11_special_member_functions/:1:3","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec11 Special Member Functions","uri":"/2023/01/lec11_special_member_functions/#move-and-move-assignment"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" Move and move assignmentMove constructors and move assignment operators will perform “memberwise moves”. Deﬁning a move assignment operator prevents generation of a move copy constructor, and vice versa. Move constructors and operators are only generated if: No copy operations are declared. No move operations are declared. No destructor is declared. If we want to explicitly support move operations, we can set the operators to default: When the item on the right of the = is an r-value we should use move assignment. r-values are always about to die, so we can steal their resources. r-value referenceDifferent with l-value reference, we use \u0026\u0026 to present r-value reference. move assignment 示例 vector\u0026 operator=(vector\u0026\u0026 other) { if (\u0026other == this) return *this; _size = other._size; _capacity = other._capacity; //we can steal the array delete[] _elems; _elems = other._elems; return *this; } std::movestd::move function mainly converts a l-value into a r-value reference. Use std::move to force the use of other types’ move assignments and constructors. 示例 vector\u0026 operator=(vector\u0026\u0026 other) { if (\u0026other == this) return *this; _size = std::move(other._size); _capacity = std::move(other._capacity); //we can steal the array delete[] _elems; _elems = std::move(other._elems); return *this; } vector vec1 = {\"hello\", \"world\"}; // vec1 = {\"hello\", \"world\"} vector vec2 = std::move(vec1); // vec2 = {\"hello\", \"world\"} // vec1 = {} vec1.push_back(\"game\"); // vec1 = {\"game\"} // `vec1` is a l-value, we use `std::move` to convert it // also break the variable `vec1` After a variable is moved via std::move, it should never be used until it is reassigned to a new variable. 警告 Don’t use std::move outside of class definitions, never use it in application code. ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec11_special_member_functions/:1:3","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec11 Special Member Functions","uri":"/2023/01/lec11_special_member_functions/#r-value-reference"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" Move and move assignmentMove constructors and move assignment operators will perform “memberwise moves”. Deﬁning a move assignment operator prevents generation of a move copy constructor, and vice versa. Move constructors and operators are only generated if: No copy operations are declared. No move operations are declared. No destructor is declared. If we want to explicitly support move operations, we can set the operators to default: When the item on the right of the = is an r-value we should use move assignment. r-values are always about to die, so we can steal their resources. r-value referenceDifferent with l-value reference, we use \u0026\u0026 to present r-value reference. move assignment 示例 vector\u0026 operator=(vector\u0026\u0026 other) { if (\u0026other == this) return *this; _size = other._size; _capacity = other._capacity; //we can steal the array delete[] _elems; _elems = other._elems; return *this; } std::movestd::move function mainly converts a l-value into a r-value reference. Use std::move to force the use of other types’ move assignments and constructors. 示例 vector\u0026 operator=(vector\u0026\u0026 other) { if (\u0026other == this) return *this; _size = std::move(other._size); _capacity = std::move(other._capacity); //we can steal the array delete[] _elems; _elems = std::move(other._elems); return *this; } vector vec1 = {\"hello\", \"world\"}; // vec1 = {\"hello\", \"world\"} vector vec2 = std::move(vec1); // vec2 = {\"hello\", \"world\"} // vec1 = {} vec1.push_back(\"game\"); // vec1 = {\"game\"} // `vec1` is a l-value, we use `std::move` to convert it // also break the variable `vec1` After a variable is moved via std::move, it should never be used until it is reassigned to a new variable. 警告 Don’t use std::move outside of class definitions, never use it in application code. ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec11_special_member_functions/:1:3","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec11 Special Member Functions","uri":"/2023/01/lec11_special_member_functions/#move-assignment"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" Move and move assignmentMove constructors and move assignment operators will perform “memberwise moves”. Deﬁning a move assignment operator prevents generation of a move copy constructor, and vice versa. Move constructors and operators are only generated if: No copy operations are declared. No move operations are declared. No destructor is declared. If we want to explicitly support move operations, we can set the operators to default: When the item on the right of the = is an r-value we should use move assignment. r-values are always about to die, so we can steal their resources. r-value referenceDifferent with l-value reference, we use \u0026\u0026 to present r-value reference. move assignment 示例 vector\u0026 operator=(vector\u0026\u0026 other) { if (\u0026other == this) return *this; _size = other._size; _capacity = other._capacity; //we can steal the array delete[] _elems; _elems = other._elems; return *this; } std::movestd::move function mainly converts a l-value into a r-value reference. Use std::move to force the use of other types’ move assignments and constructors. 示例 vector\u0026 operator=(vector\u0026\u0026 other) { if (\u0026other == this) return *this; _size = std::move(other._size); _capacity = std::move(other._capacity); //we can steal the array delete[] _elems; _elems = std::move(other._elems); return *this; } vector vec1 = {\"hello\", \"world\"}; // vec1 = {\"hello\", \"world\"} vector vec2 = std::move(vec1); // vec2 = {\"hello\", \"world\"} // vec1 = {} vec1.push_back(\"game\"); // vec1 = {\"game\"} // `vec1` is a l-value, we use `std::move` to convert it // also break the variable `vec1` After a variable is moved via std::move, it should never be used until it is reassigned to a new variable. 警告 Don’t use std::move outside of class definitions, never use it in application code. ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec11_special_member_functions/:1:3","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec11 Special Member Functions","uri":"/2023/01/lec11_special_member_functions/#stdmove"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":"CS106L 课程笔记","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec12_type_safety/","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec12 Type Safety","uri":"/2023/01/lec12_type_safety/"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" Type safetyType Safety: The extent to which a language prevents typing errors and guarantees the behavior of programs. Undeﬁned Behavior(UB): Function could crash, could give us garbage, could accidentally give us some actual value. std::optional\u003cT\u003e: A template class which will either contain a value of type T or contain nothing (expressed as nullopt). std::optional is a tool that could make this happen: you can return either a value or nothing. 示例 int main(){ std::optional\u003cint\u003e num1 = {}; // num1 does not have a value // std::optional num1 = {2}; // type deduction num1 = std::optional\u003cint\u003e{1}; // now it does! num1 = std::nullopt; // now it doesn't anymore return 0; } std::optional interface .value() returns the contained value or throws bad_optional_access error .value_or(valueType val) returns the contained value or default value(parameter val) .has_value() returns true if contained value exists, false otherwise std::optional “monadic” interface(C++23) .and_then(function f) returns the result of calling f(value) if contained value exists, otherwise null_opt (f must return optional) .or_else(function f) returns value if it exists, otherwise returns result of calling f .transform(function f) returns the result of calling f(value) if contained value exists, otherwise null_opt (f must return optional) ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec12_type_safety/:1:0","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec12 Type Safety","uri":"/2023/01/lec12_type_safety/#type-safety"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":"CS106L 课程笔记","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec13_special_topics/","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec13 Special Topics","uri":"/2023/01/lec13_special_topics/"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" RAIICode path: A single run-through of the code that the computer would see. When a function has an error, it can crash the program. This is known as “throwing an exception”. However, we can write code to handle these to let us continue. This is “catching an exception”. There are (at least) 23 code paths in the code before (1) copy constructor of Person parameter may throw (5) constructor of temp string may throw (6) call to favorite_food, favorite_drink, ﬁrst (2), last(2), may throw (10) operators may be user-overloaded, thus may throw (1) copy constructor of string for return value may throw There are many resources that need to be returned after use. RAII: Resource Acquisition is Initialization In RAII All resources used by a class should be acquired in the constructor All resources used by a class should be released in the destructor Avoid calling new and delete explicitly ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec13_special_topics/:1:0","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec13 Special Topics","uri":"/2023/01/lec13_special_topics/#raii"},{"categories":["CS106L"],"content":" Smart PointersThere are three types of smart (RAII-safe) pointers: std::unique_ptr Uniquely owns its resource, can’t be copied When a unique_ptr goes out of scope, it frees the memory associated with it std::shared_ptr Can make copies, destructed when underlying memory goes out of scope std::weak_ptr Models temporary ownership: when an object only needs to be accessed if it exists (convert to shared_ptr to access) 示例 std::unique_ptr\u003cT\u003e up{new T}; std::unique_ptr\u003cT\u003e up = std::make_unique\u003cT\u003e(); std::shared_ptr\u003cT\u003e sp{new T}; std::shared_ptr\u003cT\u003e sp = std::make_shared\u003cT\u003e(); std::weak_ptr\u003cT\u003e wp = sp; // can only be copy/move constructed(or empty) ","date":"2023-01-20","objectID":"/2023/01/lec13_special_topics/:2:0","series":null,"tags":["Cpp","公开课"],"title":"CS106L: Lec13 Special Topics","uri":"/2023/01/lec13_special_topics/#smart-pointers"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":"这是一篇 Ubuntu 的安装与配置教程，帮助你快速搭建新的系统环境（以 Ubuntu 20.04 为例）","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/setup_ubuntu/","series":null,"tags":["Linux","Tool","Shell"],"title":"从零开始搭建 Ubuntu 开发环境","uri":"/2022/08/setup_ubuntu/"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 摘要 这是一篇 Ubuntu 的安装与配置教程，帮助你快速搭建新的系统环境（以 Ubuntu 20.04 为例） ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/setup_ubuntu/:0:0","series":null,"tags":["Linux","Tool","Shell"],"title":"从零开始搭建 Ubuntu 开发环境","uri":"/2022/08/setup_ubuntu/#"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 1. 换源 cd /etc/apt # 备份原来的源 sudo cp sources.list sources.list.back sudo vim sources.list 如果没有 vim 可以使用 nano # 删除原来的源，把下面的源加进去 deb http://mirrors.aliyun.com/ubuntu/ focal main restricted deb http://mirrors.aliyun.com/ubuntu/ focal-updates main restricted deb http://mirrors.aliyun.com/ubuntu/ focal universe deb http://mirrors.aliyun.com/ubuntu/ focal-updates universe deb http://mirrors.aliyun.com/ubuntu/ focal multiverse deb http://mirrors.aliyun.com/ubuntu/ focal-updates multiverse deb http://mirrors.aliyun.com/ubuntu/ focal-backports main restricted universe multiverse deb http://mirrors.aliyun.com/ubuntu/ focal-security main restricted deb http://mirrors.aliyun.com/ubuntu/ focal-security universe deb http://mirrors.aliyun.com/ubuntu/ focal-security multiverse # 保存退出(vim) :wq # 更新一下源 sudo apt update sudo apt upgrade # 有提示输入 Y ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/setup_ubuntu/:1:0","series":null,"tags":["Linux","Tool","Shell"],"title":"从零开始搭建 Ubuntu 开发环境","uri":"/2022/08/setup_ubuntu/#1-换源"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 2. 基本环境和常用工具 sudo apt install gcc gdb cmake build-essential sudo apt install wget htop aptitude neofetch sudo apt install curl perl zip unzip aptitude ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/setup_ubuntu/:2:0","series":null,"tags":["Linux","Tool","Shell"],"title":"从零开始搭建 Ubuntu 开发环境","uri":"/2022/08/setup_ubuntu/#2-基本环境和常用工具"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 3. Zsh \u0026 oh-my-zsh # 查看当前的sehll echo $SHELL /bin/bash # 下载 zsh sudo apt install zsh -y # -y 参数会自动安装依赖 # 将默认的shell换成zsh chsh -s /bin/zsh # 重启加载(如果是WSL的话shutdown再进就行) reboot # 再次查看当前的sehll echo $SHELL /bin/zsh # 出现则说明完成安装 # 下载 oh-my-zsh sh -c \"$(wget https://raw.github.com/robbyrussell/oh-my-zsh/master/tools/install.sh -O -)\" # 下载完之后配置文件在.zshrc, 家目录下会有一个.oh-my-zsh 的文件夹 cd ~ vim .zshrc # 修改主题 ZSH_THEME=\"ys\" # 配置插件 # 1. zsh-syntax-highlighting git clone https://github.com/zsh-users/zsh-syntax-highlighting.git ${ZSH_CUSTOM:-~/.oh-my-zsh/custom}/plugins/zsh-syntax-highlighting # 2. zsh-autosuggestions git clone https://github.com/zsh-users/zsh-autosuggestions ${ZSH_CUSTOM:-~/.oh-my-zsh/custom}/plugins/zsh-autosuggestions # 3. git-open git clone https://github.com/paulirish/git-open.git ${ZSH_CUSTOM:-~/.oh-my-zsh/custom}/plugins/git-open # 在配置文件中添加插件 vim .zshrc plugins=(git z sudo extract zsh-syntax-highlighting zsh-autosuggestions git-open) source .zshrc # 禁止自动更新 vim .zshrc DISABLE_AUTO_UPDATE=\"true\" source .zshrc ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/setup_ubuntu/:3:0","series":null,"tags":["Linux","Tool","Shell"],"title":"从零开始搭建 Ubuntu 开发环境","uri":"/2022/08/setup_ubuntu/#3-zsh--oh-my-zsh"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 4. Git # 安装 git sudo apt install git # 添加git信息 git config --global user.name \"XXXX\" (换成自己的github账户) git config --global user.email \"xxxxxxx@gmail.com\" (换成自己的github邮箱) # 重置 ssh cd ~/.ssh rm known_hosts # 配置 ssh-key ssh-keygen -t rsa -C \"xxxxxxx@gmail.com\" (换成自己的github邮箱) # 一直回车就可以 # 打开 github https://github.com/ # 将 ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub 中的内容添加到ssh key中 ssh -T git@github.com # 输入 yes 后回车 ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/setup_ubuntu/:4:0","series":null,"tags":["Linux","Tool","Shell"],"title":"从零开始搭建 Ubuntu 开发环境","uri":"/2022/08/setup_ubuntu/#4-git"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 5. Vimvim 的配置文件有两个，分别对应 User 和 root，位于家目录下的 ~/.vimrc 和 /etc/vim/vimrc，一般普通用户修改 ~/.vimrc. # 可以 clone 我的配置 cd ~ git clone https://github.com/cxzhou35/Awesome-dotfiles.git ~/dotfiles mkdir -p ~/.vim/autoload cp ~/dotfiles/vim/vimscript/plug.vim ~/.vim/autoload/ cp ~/dotfiles/vim/vimscript/.vimrc ~ # 打开 vim vim # 安装配置 :PlugInstall # 会自动安装插件 # 更换主题 cp ~/dotfiles/vim/nord.vim ~/.vim/plugged/nord-vim/colors 技巧 Neovim 集成了 vim 的特性，是一个比较好的 vim 替代品，而且支持用 lua 语言配置。 链接🔗 在这里: Neovim ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/setup_ubuntu/:5:0","series":null,"tags":["Linux","Tool","Shell"],"title":"从零开始搭建 Ubuntu 开发环境","uri":"/2022/08/setup_ubuntu/#5-vim"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 6. Tmux # 安装 tmux sudo apt install tmux # 配置 git clone https://github.com/cxzhou35/Awesome-dotfiles.git ~/dotfiles # 前面操作中 clone 过的不需要再 clone cp -r ~/dotfiles/tmux ~/.tmux ln -s -f ~/.tmux/.tmux.conf cp ~/dotfiles/tmux/.tmux.conf.local ~ # 测试 tmux https://github.com/ryanoasis/nerd-fonts # 在这里下载 技巧 如果有乱码的话，是字体的问题，推荐安装 Nerd Font 链接🔗 在这里: Nerd Font ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/setup_ubuntu/:6:0","series":null,"tags":["Linux","Tool","Shell"],"title":"从零开始搭建 Ubuntu 开发环境","uri":"/2022/08/setup_ubuntu/#6-tmux"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 7. Python sudo apt install python3 python3-dev python3-pip # 设置 pip 的镜像源 mkdir ~/.pip cd ~/.pip touch pip.conf sudo vi ~/.pip/pip.conf # 添加以下内容 [global] index-url=http://mirrors.aliyun.com/pypi/simple/ [install] trusted-host=mirrors.aliyun.com ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/setup_ubuntu/:7:0","series":null,"tags":["Linux","Tool","Shell"],"title":"从零开始搭建 Ubuntu 开发环境","uri":"/2022/08/setup_ubuntu/#7-python"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 8. Conda (optional) wget https://repo.anaconda.com/miniconda/Miniconda3-latest-Linux-x86_64.sh chmod +x Miniconda3-latest-Linux-x86_64.sh ./Miniconda3-latest-Linux-x86_64.sh # 在 .zshrc 中添加环境变量 # 1. 一般conda会写到你的shell里面 source .zshrc # 2. 如果没有，手动添加以下内容 注意：zicx 改成自己的username，查看miniconda安装的路径是否一致 # \u003e\u003e\u003e conda initialize \u003e\u003e\u003e # !! Contents within this block are managed by 'conda init' !! __conda_setup=\"$('/home/zicx/miniconda3/bin/conda' 'shell.zsh' 'hook' 2\u003e /dev/null)\" if [ $? -eq 0 ]; then eval \"$__conda_setup\" else if [ -f \"/home/zicx/miniconda3/etc/profile.d/conda.sh\" ]; then . \"/home/zicx/miniconda3/etc/profile.d/conda.sh\" else export PATH=\"/home/zicx/miniconda3/bin:$PATH\" fi fi unset __conda_setup # \u003c\u003c\u003c conda initialize \u003c\u003c\u003c # 更换miniconda的源 cd ~/.conda vim .condarc # 添加以下内容 auto_activate_base: false ssl_verify: true channels: - http://mirrors.aliyun.com/anaconda/pkgs/main - http://mirrors.aliyun.com/anaconda/pkgs/r - http://mirrors.aliyun.com/anaconda/pkgs/msys2 show_channel_urls: true # 清理缓存 conda clean -a ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/setup_ubuntu/:8:0","series":null,"tags":["Linux","Tool","Shell"],"title":"从零开始搭建 Ubuntu 开发环境","uri":"/2022/08/setup_ubuntu/#8-conda-optional"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 9. 其他命令行工具 # 1. thefuck sudo pip3 install thefuck # 配置 zsh 的环境变量 vim .zshrc eval \"$(thefuck --alias fuck)\" # 添加缩写 source .zshrc # 2. fdfind cd ~/Downloads wget https://github.com/sharkdp/fd/releases/download/v8.3.2/fd_8.3.2_amd64.deb sudo dpkg -i fd_8.3.2_amd64.deb rm fd_8.3.2_amd64.deb # 3. bat cd ~/Downloads wget https://github.com/sharkdp/bat/releases/download/v0.21.0/bat_0.21.0_amd64.deb sudo dpkg -i bat_0.21.0_amd64.deb ## ubuntu18.04 用musl版本的 wget https://github.com/sharkdp/bat/releases/download/v0.21.0/bat-musl_0.21.0_amd64.deb rm bat_0.21.0_amd64.deb # 在 zsh 中添加配置 vim .zshrc alias cat=\"bat\" # 添加缩写 export BAT_THEME=\"Solarized (light)\" # 更改主题 source .zshrc # 4. fzf (结合 vim 使用无敌) ## 通过 git 安装 git clone --depth 1 https://github.com/junegunn/fzf.git ~/.fzf cd ~/.fzf/ ./install ## 通过 dpkg 安装 cd ~/Downloads wget http://cn.archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu/pool/universe/f/fzf/fzf_0.30.0-1_amd64.deb sudo dpkg -i fzf_0.30.0-1_amd64.deb rm fzf_0.30.0-1_amd64.deb ## 更新fzf cd ~/.fzf \u0026\u0026 git pull \u0026\u0026 ./install # 5. ncdu sudo apt install ncdu # 6. nnn cd ~/Downloads git clone https://github.com/jarun/nnn.git cd nnn sudo make O_NERD=1 ./nnn sudo mv ~/Downloads/nnn/nnn /bin/ # 7. tldr sudo apt install tldr # 8. exa ## 安装 rust curl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 -sSf https://sh.rustup.rs | sh mkdir ~/Downloads/exa wget https://github.com/ogham/exa/releases/download/v0.10.1/exa-linux-x86_64-v0.10.1.zip ~/Downloads/exa unzip exa-linux-x86_64-v0.10.1.zip sudo mv exa /usr/local/bin/ # 验证exa exa -v # 替换ls vim .zshrc alias ls=\"exa\" source .zshrc # 9. ranger pip install ranger-fm or sudo apt install ranger ranger --copy-config=all # 安装预览插件 sudo apt install poppler sudo apt install highlight sudo apt install mediainfo sudo apt install ueberzug sudo apt install w3m-img sudo apt install libx11-dev sudo apt install libxext-dev sudo pip3 install ueberzug # 配置环境变量 export RANGER_LOAD_DEFAULT_RC=FALSE # 图标显示 git clone https://github.com/alexanderjeurissen/ranger_devicons ~/.config/ranger/plugins/ranger_devicons git clone https://github.com/cxzhou35/Awesome-dotfiles.git ~/dotfiles # 前面操作中clone过的不需要再clone cp ~/dotfiles/ranger/rc.conf ~/.config/ranger/conf # 10. lazygit ```bash sudo add-apt-repository ppa:lazygit-team/release sudo apt update sudo apt install lazygit # 添加缩写 echo \"alias lg=\"lazygit\"\" \u003e\u003e ~/.zshrc ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/setup_ubuntu/:9:0","series":null,"tags":["Linux","Tool","Shell"],"title":"从零开始搭建 Ubuntu 开发环境","uri":"/2022/08/setup_ubuntu/#9-其他命令行工具"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 番外一些有意思的终端工具 sudo apt install sl # 小火车 sudo apt install cmatrix # 字符雨 sudo apt install xcowsay # 奶牛 sudo apt install aview # ascii格式打开图片 asciiview test.png sudo apt install lolcat # 终端颜色真值输出 neofetch | lolcat # 测试 sudo apt install figlet # 字符串转字符画 持续更新中…… 📆 信息 想要了解更多其他系统的配置内容，可以到这个 Github Wiki 查看哦🫰🏼 ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/setup_ubuntu/:10:0","series":null,"tags":["Linux","Tool","Shell"],"title":"从零开始搭建 Ubuntu 开发环境","uri":"/2022/08/setup_ubuntu/#番外"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":"这是一篇 Markdown 的简易教程，本人在写博客的过程中，经常发现自己会忘记一些语法，因此专门写下这篇文章来记录一下，以便以后遇到问题时能够更快速地查阅。","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/markdown_use/","series":null,"tags":["Markdown","Hugo"],"title":"Markdown 教程与 Hugo 中的简单应用","uri":"/2022/08/markdown_use/"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 摘要 这是一篇 Markdown 的简易教程，本人在写博客的过程中，经常发现自己会忘记一些语法，因此专门写下这篇文章来记录一下，以便以后遇到问题时能够更快速地查阅。 ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/markdown_use/:0:0","series":null,"tags":["Markdown","Hugo"],"title":"Markdown 教程与 Hugo 中的简单应用","uri":"/2022/08/markdown_use/#"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 1. 标题多级标题使用 # 号 来定义，一个 # 号表示一级标题，两个 # 号表示二级标题， 依次类推，最多支持六级标题。 下面是一些例子： # Level 1 ## Level 2 ### Level 3 #### Level 4 ##### Level 5 ###### Level 6 ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/markdown_use/:1:0","series":null,"tags":["Markdown","Hugo"],"title":"Markdown 教程与 Hugo 中的简单应用","uri":"/2022/08/markdown_use/#1-标题"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 2. 字体及段落","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/markdown_use/:2:0","series":null,"tags":["Markdown","Hugo"],"title":"Markdown 教程与 Hugo 中的简单应用","uri":"/2022/08/markdown_use/#2-字体及段落"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 2.1 斜体在需要使用 斜体 部分的前后使用一个 号或者下划线 _ 标记，可以使字体表现为斜体* 。 注意 需要注意的是，在使用中文字体时，* 号或者下划线 _ 和正常字体中间需要一个空格，否则最后会表现为_斜体_。 ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/markdown_use/:2:1","series":null,"tags":["Markdown","Hugo"],"title":"Markdown 教程与 Hugo 中的简单应用","uri":"/2022/08/markdown_use/#21-斜体"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 2.2 加粗在需要使用 加粗 部分的前后使用两个 * 号标记，可以使字体表现为 加粗 。 ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/markdown_use/:2:2","series":null,"tags":["Markdown","Hugo"],"title":"Markdown 教程与 Hugo 中的简单应用","uri":"/2022/08/markdown_use/#22-加粗"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 2.3 删除线在需要使用 删除线 部分的前后使用两个~号标记，可以使字体表现为 删除线 。 ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/markdown_use/:2:3","series":null,"tags":["Markdown","Hugo"],"title":"Markdown 教程与 Hugo 中的简单应用","uri":"/2022/08/markdown_use/#23-删除线"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 2.4 高亮在需要使用 ==高亮== 部分的前后使用两个 = 号标记，可以使字体表现为 ==高亮== 。 警告⚠️ 这个高亮语法是 Typora 里面才有的，不在 Markdown 官方语法中。 提示 上面提到的4种标记方式可以一起使用，比如使用三个 * 号标记，可以使字体表现为 粗斜体。 ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/markdown_use/:2:4","series":null,"tags":["Markdown","Hugo"],"title":"Markdown 教程与 Hugo 中的简单应用","uri":"/2022/08/markdown_use/#24-高亮"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 2.5 下划线下划线部分，其语法为 \u003cins\u003e下划线部分\u003c/ins\u003e ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/markdown_use/:2:5","series":null,"tags":["Markdown","Hugo"],"title":"Markdown 教程与 Hugo 中的简单应用","uri":"/2022/08/markdown_use/#25-下划线"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 2.6 上标上标内容，其语法为 \u003csup\u003e上标的内容\u003c/sup\u003e ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/markdown_use/:2:6","series":null,"tags":["Markdown","Hugo"],"title":"Markdown 教程与 Hugo 中的简单应用","uri":"/2022/08/markdown_use/#26-上标"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 2.7 下标下标内容，其语法为 \u003csub\u003e下标的内容\u003c/sub\u003e ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/markdown_use/:2:7","series":null,"tags":["Markdown","Hugo"],"title":"Markdown 教程与 Hugo 中的简单应用","uri":"/2022/08/markdown_use/#27-下标"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 2.8 按键按键，其语法为 \u003ckbd\u003e按键\u003c/kbd\u003e ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/markdown_use/:2:8","series":null,"tags":["Markdown","Hugo"],"title":"Markdown 教程与 Hugo 中的简单应用","uri":"/2022/08/markdown_use/#28-按键"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 2.9 链接插入链接 百度，其语法为 [文字] (链接) 点击一下试试 404 not Found 注意 ] 和 ( 之间没有空格，这里是为了方便说明语法，避免渲染。 使用尖括号 \u003c \u003e 可以很方便地把 URL 或者 Email 地址变成可点击的链接。 \u003chttps://baidu.cn\u003e \u003cxxx@example.com\u003e ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/markdown_use/:2:9","series":null,"tags":["Markdown","Hugo"],"title":"Markdown 教程与 Hugo 中的简单应用","uri":"/2022/08/markdown_use/#29-链接"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 2.10 Admonitionadmonition 是 Hugo 的特殊 Markdown shortcut，其语法为 {{ \u003c admonition type=tip title=\"This is a tip\" open=false \u003e}} content {{ \u003c /admonition \u003e}} admonition shortcode 有以下命名参数： type [必需]（第一个位置参数） admonition 横幅的类型，默认值是 note。 可以用以下的 tpye tip：提示 note：笔记 abstract：摘要 info：信息 success：成功 failure：失败 question：问题 warning：警告 danger：危险 bug：bug example：示例 quote： 引用 title [可选]（第二个位置参数） admonition 横幅的标题，默认值是 type 参数的值。（支持 markdown） open [可选]（第三个位置参数） 横幅内容是否默认展开，默认值是 true ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/markdown_use/:2:10","series":null,"tags":["Markdown","Hugo"],"title":"Markdown 教程与 Hugo 中的简单应用","uri":"/2022/08/markdown_use/#210-admonition"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 3. 列表","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/markdown_use/:3:0","series":null,"tags":["Markdown","Hugo"],"title":"Markdown 教程与 Hugo 中的简单应用","uri":"/2022/08/markdown_use/#3-列表"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 3.1 无序列表 level 1.1 level 2.1 level 3.1 无序列表支持多级显示，可以使用 * 或者 - 来实现，其语法为 # 可以使用 - 或者 * ，- 或者 * 也可以混用 - level 1.1 - level 2.1 - level 3.1 * level 1.1 * level 2.1 * level 3.1 ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/markdown_use/:3:1","series":null,"tags":["Markdown","Hugo"],"title":"Markdown 教程与 Hugo 中的简单应用","uri":"/2022/08/markdown_use/#31--无序列表"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 3.2 有序列表 level 1.1 level 2.1 level 3.1 有序列表支持多级显示，使用 数字 + . 来实现，其语法为 1. level 1.1 1. level 2.1 1. level 3.1 ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/markdown_use/:3:2","series":null,"tags":["Markdown","Hugo"],"title":"Markdown 教程与 Hugo 中的简单应用","uri":"/2022/08/markdown_use/#32-有序列表"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 3.3 任务列表 aaa bbb ccc 任务列表也支持多级显示，使用 - [ ] 或者 - [x] 来实现，其语法为 - [ ] aaa - [ ] bbb - [x] ccc ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/markdown_use/:3:3","series":null,"tags":["Markdown","Hugo"],"title":"Markdown 教程与 Hugo 中的简单应用","uri":"/2022/08/markdown_use/#33-任务列表"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 4. 引用块 1 2 3 引用可以支持多级引用，使用 \u003e 来实现，其语法为 # 每级引用需要有空行 \u003e 1 \u003e\u003e 2 \u003e\u003e\u003e 3 ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/markdown_use/:4:0","series":null,"tags":["Markdown","Hugo"],"title":"Markdown 教程与 Hugo 中的简单应用","uri":"/2022/08/markdown_use/#4-引用块"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 5. 代码块 #include \u003cstdio.h\u003e int main(void){ printf(\"Hello World!\\n); return 0; } 对于代码块，需要在代码块前后使用三个 ` 来将代码块围起来，并且可以在开始的 ``` 后指定语言，例如 C、Python、Java 等。 ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/markdown_use/:5:0","series":null,"tags":["Markdown","Hugo"],"title":"Markdown 教程与 Hugo 中的简单应用","uri":"/2022/08/markdown_use/#5-代码块"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 6. 图片Markdown 的图片的格式为 ![ ]( ) 提示 Markdown 支持 HTML 语法，可以对多种对象操作，下面是一个图片设置居中的例子。 \u003cdiv align=center\u003e \u003cimg src=\"path\"/\u003e \u003c/div\u003e 提示 Hugo 也有特殊的语法，可以对多种对象操作，下面是一个用 Hugo 插入图片的例子。 # 可以添加图片名称 {{ % figure class=\"center\" src=\"images.png\" alt=\"图1\" title=\"图1\" %}} ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/markdown_use/:6:0","series":null,"tags":["Markdown","Hugo"],"title":"Markdown 教程与 Hugo 中的简单应用","uri":"/2022/08/markdown_use/#6-图片"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 7. 表格Markdown 中表格使用 | 来分隔不同的单元格，使用 - 来分隔表头和其他行，通过 : 号和 - 的相对位置可以来设置表格的对齐方式。 :- 左对齐 -: 右对齐 :-: 居中 下面是一个表格的例子 左对齐 居中 右对齐 1 1 1 2 2 2 源码如下 | 左对齐 | 居中| 右对齐 | |:------ |:------:| ----:| | 1 | 1 | 1 | | 2 | 2 | 2 | ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/markdown_use/:7:0","series":null,"tags":["Markdown","Hugo"],"title":"Markdown 教程与 Hugo 中的简单应用","uri":"/2022/08/markdown_use/#7-表格"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 8. 公式 注意 Hugo 的公式渲染有时候会出现 bug，若公式没有渲染请刷新页面重新查看。 ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/markdown_use/:8:0","series":null,"tags":["Markdown","Hugo"],"title":"Markdown 教程与 Hugo 中的简单应用","uri":"/2022/08/markdown_use/#8-公式"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 8.1 行内公式$\\partial_t v - \\frac{1}{\\rho}\\partial_x \\tau = 0$, 行内公式的语法为 $ \\partial_t v - \\frac{1}{\\rho}\\partial_x \\tau = 0 $ ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/markdown_use/:8:1","series":null,"tags":["Markdown","Hugo"],"title":"Markdown 教程与 Hugo 中的简单应用","uri":"/2022/08/markdown_use/#81-行内公式"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 8.2 行间公式$$ \\partial_t v - \\frac{1}{\\rho}\\partial_x \\tau = 0 $$ 行间公式的语法为 $$ \\partial_t v - \\frac{1}{\\rho}\\partial_x \\tau = 0 $$ ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/markdown_use/:8:2","series":null,"tags":["Markdown","Hugo"],"title":"Markdown 教程与 Hugo 中的简单应用","uri":"/2022/08/markdown_use/#82-行间公式"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 8.3 矩阵 a. 普通矩阵$$ \\begin{matrix} 0 \u0026 1 \\\\ 1 \u0026 0 \\end{matrix} $$ 源码如下 $$ \\begin{matrix} 0 \u0026 1 \\\\\\\\ 1 \u0026 0 \\end{matrix} $$ b. 圆括号矩阵$$ \\begin{pmatrix} 0 \u0026 1 \\\\ 1 \u0026 0 \\end{pmatrix} $$ 源码如下 $$ \\begin{pmatrix} 0 \u0026 1 \\\\\\\\ 1 \u0026 0 \\end{pmatrix} $$ c. 方括号矩阵$$ \\begin{bmatrix} 0 \u0026 1 \\\\ 1 \u0026 0 \\end{bmatrix} $$ 源码如下 $$ \\begin{bmatrix} 0 \u0026 1 \\\\\\\\ 1 \u0026 0 \\end{bmatrix} $$ c. 大括号矩阵$$ \\begin{Bmatrix} 0 \u0026 1 \\\\ 1 \u0026 0 \\end{Bmatrix} $$ 源码如下 $$ \\begin{Bmatrix} 0 \u0026 1 \\\\\\\\ 1 \u0026 0 \\end{Bmatrix} $$ 注意 LaTeX 的换行符为 \\，但是这里使用的是 \\\\，主要是因为 Markdown 中的两个 \\ 才表示一个 \\，因此在换行时需要使用4个 \\。 ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/markdown_use/:8:3","series":null,"tags":["Markdown","Hugo"],"title":"Markdown 教程与 Hugo 中的简单应用","uri":"/2022/08/markdown_use/#83-矩阵"},{"categories":["教程"],"content":" 8.3 矩阵 a. 普通矩阵$$ \\begin{matrix} 0 \u0026 1 \\\\ 1 \u0026 0 \\end{matrix} $$ 源码如下 $$ \\begin{matrix} 0 \u0026 1 \\\\\\\\ 1 \u0026 0 \\end{matrix} $$ b. 圆括号矩阵$$ \\begin{pmatrix} 0 \u0026 1 \\\\ 1 \u0026 0 \\end{pmatrix} $$ 源码如下 $$ \\begin{pmatrix} 0 \u0026 1 \\\\\\\\ 1 \u0026 0 \\end{pmatrix} $$ c. 方括号矩阵$$ \\begin{bmatrix} 0 \u0026 1 \\\\ 1 \u0026 0 \\end{bmatrix} $$ 源码如下 $$ \\begin{bmatrix} 0 \u0026 1 \\\\\\\\ 1 \u0026 0 \\end{bmatrix} $$ c. 大括号矩阵$$ \\begin{Bmatrix} 0 \u0026 1 \\\\ 1 \u0026 0 \\end{Bmatrix} $$ 源码如下 $$ \\begin{Bmatrix} 0 \u0026 1 \\\\\\\\ 1 \u0026 0 \\end{Bmatrix} $$ 注意 LaTeX 的换行符为 \\，但是这里使用的是 \\\\，主要是因为 Markdown 中的两个 \\ 才表示一个 \\，因此在换行时需要使用4个 \\。 ","date":"2022-08-18","objectID":"/2022/08/markdown_use/:8:3","series":null,"tags":["Markdown","Hugo"],"title":"Markdown 教程与 Hugo 中的简单应用","uri":"/2022/08/markdown_use/#a-普通矩阵"},{"categori